{#@@
    This dotfile simply includes the right content from other dotfiles based
    on system variables like machine or user.

    The mutually exclusive inclusion of machine-specific and user-specific
    mrtrust files is by design. In fact, this allows the machine-specific
    mrtrust file to completely override the user-specific one, while it is
    still possible for the former to manually include the latter if necessary.
    Conversely, this would not be possible if both the files were included
    top-level here.
@@#}
{%@@ include [
    'config/mr/mrtrust.%s.%s' | format(env['MACHINE'], user),
    'config/mr/mrtrust.%s' | format(user)
] ignore missing @@%}
